==English==

===Etymology===
Imitative.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To produce the a harsh scraping, grating sound, as of friction.
## To make sounds such as of a chair on the floor or chalk on a blackboard.
##* {{quote-book|lang=en|author=Siegfried Sassoon|authorlink=Siegfried Sassoon
|title=[[w:Sherston's Progress|Sherston's Progress]]
|location=London|publisher=Faber|year=1937|page=628 (in The Complete Memoirs of George Sherston )
|passage=I exclaimed in a loud voice, '''scrooping''' back my chair on the brick floor and standing up.}}
## To produce a rustling sound, like that from friction between silk fibers.
##: ''The friction causes the silk to '''scroop'''.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A rustling sound like that produced from friction between silk fibers.

